ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Details of the materials and the proportions of grout mixture shall be submitted for review. Product to be selected based on the following criteria:
i. have the required strength at 28 days as noted on the IFC drawings.
ii. have the characteristics capable of being applied to the minimum and maximum thickness as noted on the IFC drawings.
FREQUENCY: Once, for each product, prior to placement of product
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Precast supplier is required to provide the following Quality Assurance documentation for each element, typically this consists of:
i. Certificate of Compliance / Birth Certificate
viii. Record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate compliance with dimensional tolerances of precast and bearing plates (where applicable) shown on table 610.473
Note: Different revisions of 610 have different clause numbers
Collate: Precast Quality Assurance Documentation so it can be uploaded into Teambinder (don't attach it here)
4.1 Precast Element - Minimum Concrete Compressive Strength
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Lifting of precast units to be minimum concrete compressive strength of 20 Mpa.
• Ancon lifting design requires minimum concrete compressive strength of 30 Mpa.
• Verify compressive strength test results prior to lift.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Revision of the IFC drawings are current as per the drawing register (on Teambinder)
FREQUENCY: Prior to starting Works and at regular intervals

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Survey activities undertaken to ensure and validate that all Works meet level and location requirements within the tolerances as per the Table 610.473 as applicable to the element.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Construction joints shall be prepared to produce a well-bonded interface between hardened concrete and freshly placed concrete.
• 3mm of coarse aggregate to be exposed.
• Surface to be moistened, with excess water removed.
REFERENCE: IFC Drawings, Temporary Works, Table 610.472
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Place packers to the survey marks at each column in accordance with approved temporary works and tolerances.
• Scabbled surface to be levelled where packers to be placed.
• Packers to be checked for survey tolerance of crosshead reduced level. (±10mm for reduced level for piers as per 610.472 (ix))
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Minimum 3 No.Bleed tubes per pile are installed
REFERENCE: IFC Drawings, Product TDS / Application Guide
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Seal perimeter of column, excluding 3 No. min bleed tubes per column to be equally spaced.
• Thin layer of wax compound to be applied to forms to minimise grout sticking.
• Do NOT pre-soak when using resin based grouts.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Grout tubes are inserted to the bottom of the corrugated sheath (Duct)
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Unless otherwise specified, precast elements shall be lifted using the lifting points provided and supported with the top surface uppermost at all times.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Precast elements shall be placed onto the bearing shims and not released from the crane until sufficiently braced in accordance with the approved temporary works design and/or IFC drawings.
○ The Gap between precast crosshead and pile
REFERENCE: Manufacturer Instruction, Product TDS / Application Guide
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Pour the entire contents of the hardener pack into the base container. Mix the hardener slowly into the base using a slow speed heavy duty mixer.
• Once combined the product should be mixed at 350 to 400 RPM for 2 to 3 minutes until a uniform mix is obtained.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Grout allowed to flow until all bleed water is expelled and grout flows freely from each bleed tube. Then lock off bleed tube.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Grout injected in a continuous pour until grout emerges from the top of all ducts
VERIFYING DOCUMENTS: This ITP -Grout Pour Checklist
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Three (3) 75 mm test cubes shall be taken from the first batch of material mixed.
• Three (3) 75 mm cubes for every 100 kg of material used thereafter to test for compressive strength.
• The cubes shall be cured for seven days under laboratory-controlled conditions
• Test cubes shall be made in rigid steel moulds, cured and tested in accordance with AS 1478.2.
• The contact face of the concrete shall be flat and have a surface roughness between an amplitude of 0.5 mm to 1.5 mm, with a surface presenting similar to Grade 40 grit sandpaper.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Two (2) cubes shall be tested at seven days and the third cube at 28 days to confirm compliance with the minimum compressive strength requirements.
• The minimum compressive strength of test cubes shall be50mpa At 28 days.

ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Provide record of dimensional measurements to demonstrate concrete members comply with tolerances as per the table 610.462 (November 2018) or 610.472 (March/June 2019) as applicable to the element.
ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA: Ensure that any NCRs pertaining to the lot / element / Work area that this ITP covers, have been closed in CAMs.
FREQUENCY: Once, prior to closure of this lot / element / Work area

On behalf of Metropolitan Roads Program Alliance, it is hereby certified that the Works represented by the item of work listed have been tested in accordance with the Project Quality Plan and conform in all respects with the requirements of the Contract.
